TCP (protocol)
->
TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) is a transport-layer protocol that provides a reliable, ordered, error-checked stream of bytes between two devices over a network.

If HTTP is the language you speak and WebSocket is the conversation style, then TCP is the telephone line carrying everything.

Simple analogy

Imagine sending a 100-page document to a friend.

Without TCP:

Pages might arrive out of order.
Some pages might never arrive.
Some pages might arrive twice.
You wouldn't know.

With TCP:

Every page is numbered.
The receiver confirms what was received.
Missing pages are resent.
Pages are put back in the correct order.

So the receiver gets the exact same 100-page document.



